wiki.summary: Polo G enlists NLE Choppa and Stunna 4 Vegas for “Go Stupid,” his second 2020 single following January’s “First Place.” The three artists, who all saw their popularity skyrocket throughout 2019, team up for the first time over hard-hitting production from star producers Tay Keith and Mike WiLL Made-It. The single was announced on Instagram two days before its release on Valentine’s Day alongside an accompanying music video. The single peaked at #60 on the Billboard Hot 100. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: Polo G enlists NLE Choppa and Stunna 4 Vegas for “Go Stupid,” his second 2020 single following January’s “First Place.” The three artists, who all saw their popularity skyrocket throughout 2019, team up for the first time over hard-hitting production from star producers Tay Keith and Mike WiLL Made-It. The single was announced on Instagram two days before its release on Valentine’s Day alongside an accompanying music video. The single peaked at #60 on the Billboard Hot 100. This earned Polo G his second career Hot 100 entry, after his breakout single “Pop Out.” On May 6, 2020, the single earned a gold certification from RIAA. Read more on Last.fm.
